The paper discusses advanced reasoning techniques and knowledge discovery in General Game Playing (GGP), which falls under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The use of genetic algorithms for parameter tweaking and self-play also suggests a connection to Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with game theory (cs.GT) and propositional logic (cs.PL) in the context of GGP. Finally, the development of a GGP framework suggests a connection to Systems and Control (cs.SY).
